<br>
Anyway, if you weren't on Saturday evening, you missed us and a few of the Ares' Fury folks going into the Hole after the Scalekeeper for Zemlya's red scale.  So I'll run this guy down for you, since I know -exactly- what he does, having been the main tank for the venture:<br>
<br>
1.  High Cheatery:  Scalekeeper procs a 1500 point lifetap.  He doesn't cast it, he PROCS it, and it happens about every other swing.  I resisted around half of them with an MR of around 370 (They were attempted on me well over 60 times), but died when he proc'd four of them in a row for nearly max damage.<br>
<br>
2.  Hit Points:  He doesn't have all that many, but he is constantly thieving them from the main tank, which makes it seem like he's got alot.<br>
<br>
3.  AE:  He area affects a weak harm touch-like spell.  It only happened once, and most if not all of us resisted it, at least in my group<br>
<br>
4.  Key to this guy:  DAMAGE!  We need as many damage dealing blast and stab monkeys as we can muster.  We most likely would have had him had we been able to slow him as well, but my slow wouldn't stick to him, and nobody in the raid could cripple and all that, so he was at full attack the entire fight.  We gotta be very, very careful on this guy with aggro, though, he's definitely a mage killer.  He averaged proccing that lifetap twice per attack, which adds up if you took full damage to around 3600 damage a round. (he double attacks for around 275ish)<br>
<br>
If its possible, later tonight would be a good chance to go back after him, as I doubt anyone will have killed him by then.  Try to get on this afternoon if you can, I'll be on at 3:00pm eastern up until I pass out sometime very early Monday morning and will try somewhat to coordinate the venture, although I'll need someone who knows their way there better than I do.  Let's get this guy, he owes me a tic of exp and a red dragon scale for whippin' my ass yesterday!<br>
<br>
